\layout Standard

order: Tx+z-, Tx+z+, Tx-z-, Tx-z+
\layout Standard

Tx-z- and Tx-z+ should be close to the shed temperature.
\layout Standard

Tx+z- and Tx+z+ depend on the probe position, as the gap (iron yoke) is
 warmer
\layout Standard

than the shed and the dipole coil (at both ends of the dipole) is warmer
\layout Standard

than the iron yoke.
 For a probe in a central position for
\layout Standard

more than about one hour, the Tx+z- and Tx+z+ sensors should
\layout Standard

give the yoke temperature, i.e the shed temperature plus 0.
 to 5.C, depending
\layout Standard

on the current, LCW temperature and the magnet/shed temperature history.
